Control statement
------------------
The statement or instructions are used to inform the computer to perform the task when a program is being executed.

Types of control statement : 
a. Sequential control statement 
   Input ----------- Process --------------- Output
             (Formula Implementation)
   Ex : p,r,t     SI = (p*r*t)/100      o/p : si 
   Ex : f         c = (f-32)*5/9        o/p : c 

b. Conditional control statement 
   (Decision control statement) 
   i. if statement 
      syntax : 
            if(condition){
                statement 1 to n
            }

   ii. if else statement 
      syntax : 
            if(condition){
               statement 1 to n
            }else{
               statement 1 to n
            }

   iii. nested if else statement 
      syntax : 
            if(condition){
               statement 1 to n
            }else{
               if(condition){
                  statement 1 to n
               }else{
                  statement 1 to n  
               }  
            }

   iv. else if ladder 
   Syntax : 
            if(condition)
               statement 1 to n
            else if(condition)  
               statement 1 to n
            else if(condition)  
               statement 1 to n
            else if(condition)  
               statement 1 to n
            else 
               statement 1 to n


c. Switch control statement 
   It is mainly used for menu based programming.
   It works on the concept of cases. 

            x           5         n%2 
   switch(variable | constant | expression){
      case 'a' : 
            break;
      case 1 : 
            break;
      case "Red" : 
            break;
      case 'A' :
            break;
      default : 
            break;
   }

d. Looping control statement 

